Name: Darden Bridgeforth & Sons
Description: "Bridgeforth International (BI) is family-owned and operated in  Tanner Alabama . Since BI opened in 2012, we’ve treated every customer like they were a part of our family. Our exclusive partnership with Darden Bridgeforth and Sons, allows us to provide high quality products which are locally grown by experienced farmers."

Name: Fountain Heights Farm
Description: "The mission of Fountain Heights Farms is to improve the quality of life for the current residents of the historic Fountain Heights community of Birmingham, Alabama through long term land stewardship by community-led urban agricultural cooperatives focused on meeting the immediate and basic need for healthy fresh foods, and through culturally responsive community education programs that support and inform urban agricultural initiatives in historically under-served areas of Birmingham, Alabama."

Name: Bright Star Community Development Corp
Sheet Description: Bright Star Community Development Corp // AZ
Description: "Providing Resources & Services to Enrich, Empower and Improve Lives. Monthly Food Pantry. In Partnership with Southern AZ Community Food Bank/TUSD Backpack Program. Bright Star CDC engages in special care projects that will make a difference"

Name: Patagonia Flower Farm
Description: "The foundation of a healthy micro-farm starts with biologically diverse fields and healthy soil. Operated since 2017, Patagonia Flower Farm is your local source for fresh flowers that are never imported. Our organic practices are as healthy for the Earth as they are for your home and office."

Name: Tiger Mountain Foundation
Description: "The TigerMountain Foundation (TMF) plants fruits & veggies while cultivating better communities. This is done through community garden volunteer work. Our multi-cultural, inter-generational Asset Based Community Development (ABCD) means we don’t give a handout, we give the community a hand up."

Name: African American Farmers of California demo farm
Sheet Description: African American Farmers of California demo farm // CA
Description: "The mission of the African American Farmers of California (AAFCA) is to increase within the African American Community an appreciation and understanding of applied resource management through the promotion of sound farmland management, technology, community marketing, and outreach to urban and rural areas."

Name: Afrika Town Community Garden
Description: "An urban haven in West Oakland, Afrika Town at Qilombo empowers community members via food sustainability, justice, self-defense training and self-care."

Name: City Heights Farmers Market
Description: "A True Multi-Cultural Urban Farmers' Market in the Heart of East San Diego City. We match CalFresh/EBT benefits! Double your food dollars with Market Match. Get up to $10 for FREE to spend on produce each week. Fresh fruits and vegetables, hot food vendors, arts and crafts, health programs, live entertainment, children's activities and more!"

Name: City Slicker Farms
Description: "City Slicker Farms began with a mission to empower West Oakland community members to meet the basic need for fresh, healthy food by creating sustainable, high-yield urban farms and backyard gardens. Since its founding in 2001, City Slicker Farms has been at the forefront of the 21st-century sustainable urban farming and food justice movement, gaining national recognition as a leader in supporting low-income communities of color to grow food in the city. In those sixteen years, we have built over 400 backyard and community gardens, produced 300,000 pounds of nutrient rich food, and trained thousands of community members in organic gardening methods and environmental stewardship."

Name: Community Services Unlimited
Description: "Community Services Unlimited Inc. (CSU), is a 501c3 established in 1977 and head quartered in South Central Los Angeles. Since then it has created community programs and organizing campaigns like the early Safe Seniors to the more recent Free Medical Screening Program and the most recent From the Ground Up. CSU has also provided fiscal sponsorship and support for many grass roots organizing efforts ranging in diversity from Police Watch, Community in Support of the Gang Truce, and Food Forestry International."

Name: Crop Swap LA
Description: "Volunteer run since October 2018, first under the name West Adams Crop Swap, Crop Swap LA invites gardeners across Los Angeles to bring their extra veggies, fruits, herbs, and valuable homemade items to trade whatever they wish. The abundance was enormous, and we got to thinking about ways to form infrastructures to harvest it ongoing."

Black Urban Gardeners and Farmers of Pittsburgh Co-op
Divine Natural Ancestry
Description: "Divine Natural Ancestry is a collective of three spiritual kinfolk living on Dakota and Anishinaabe land. We are dedicated to choosing life, love, healing through Radical Liberation. We are stewards of the earth, healers, creators, warriors, and visionaries. We are called to use our gifts to continue our ancestors Revolution and heal trauma both interpersonally and communally."
